description: Coined by A. B. Dick in 1889 and originally a trade name. From Ancient Greek μῖμος (mîmos), combining form mimeo +‎ -graph.

entries.meaning: (historical) A machine for making printed copies using typed stencil, eventually superseded by photocopying.

verbs.description: mimeograph (third-person singular simple present mimeographs, present participle mimeographing, simple past and past participle mimeographed)
